{{see|Crater|cráter}}
==English==

===Etymology===
From {{L.}} '''crater''', a "[[basin]]"

===Pronunciation===
*Rhymes: [[Rhymes:English:-eɪtə(r)|-eɪtə(r)]]

===Noun===
{{en-noun}}

# {{astronomy}}: A [[hemispherical]] [[pit]] created by the [[impact]] of a [[meteor]] or other object.
# {{geology}}: The basinlike opening or mouth of a [[volcano]], through which the chief [[eruption]] comes; similarly, the mouth of a [[geyser]], about which a cone of silica is often built up.
# The pit left by the explosion of a [[mine]].

